==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Old Norse ''þrǽll'' (Danish [[træl]], Swedish [[träll]]), perhaps from Proto-Norse ''*þrāhilaR'', from Germanic ''*þrāhiloz'', from ''*þreh-'' ‘to run’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /θɹæ:l/

===Noun===
'''þrǣl''' ''m'' (''pl'' '''þrǣlas''')
# a [[slave]], someone beholden to a [[lord]] or [[master]]

